{{Infobox scientist | name = Peter Francis Stevens | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 1944 | birth_place = [[United Kingdom]] | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | other_names = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = British | fields = Botany | workplaces = * [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] * [[University of Missouri–St. Louis]] | patrons = | education = [[Oxford University]] | alma_mater = | thesis_title = <!--(or | thesis1_title = and | thesis2_title = )--> | thesis_url = <!--(or | thesis1_url = and | thesis2_url = )--> | thesis_year = <!--(or | thesis1_year = and | thesis2_year = )--> | doctoral_advisor = <!--(or | doctoral_advisors = )--> | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = [[APG system|APG]] | influences = | influenced = | awards = | author_abbrev_bot = P.F.Stevens | author_abbrev_zoo = | spouse = | partner = <!--(or | partners = )--> | children = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = }}
'''Peter Francis Stevens''' is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[botanist]] born in 1944.
He is a [[researcher]] at the [[Missouri Botanical Garden]] and professor of Biology of the [[University of Missouri–St. Louis]]. He is a member of the [[Angiosperm Phylogeny Group]] which created the [[APG system|APG]], [[APG II system|APG II]], [[APG III system|APG III]], and [[APG IV system|APG IV]] systems.
He maintains a web site, [[Angiosperm Phylogeny Website|APweb]], hosted by the Missouri Botanical Garden, which has been regularly updated since 2001, and is a useful source for the latest research in angiosperm phylogeny which follows the APG approach.<ref>Commended by, e.g., [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Taxonomy/taxonomyhome.html/index.cgi?chapter=resources NCBI] and [http://www.kew.org/msbp/faq/useful_links.html Kew] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090214225643/http://www.kew.org/msbp/faq/useful_links.html |date=2009-02-14 }}.</ref>
The standard [[List of botanists by author abbreviation|author abbreviation]] '''P.F.Stevens''' is used to indicate P. F. Stevens as the author when [[Author citation (botany)|citing]] a [[botanical name]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ipni.org/ipni/idAuthorSearch.do?id=10130-1 |title=Stevens, Peter Francis (1944–) |work=Author Details |publisher=[[International Plant Names Index]] |accessdate=March 9, 2012}}</ref> He has named dozens of species, mostly in the families [[Clusiaceae]] and [[Ericaceae]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.biologie.uni-hamburg.de/b-online/ibc99/missouri/Stevens.html |title=Peter F. Stevens |publisher=[[University of Hamburg|Universität Hamburg]] |accessdate=March 9, 2012}}</ref> and he also described the genus ''[[Romnalda]]'' ([[Asparagaceae]]).<ref>{{cite journal |author=R. J. F. Henderson |year=1982 |title=''Romnalda grallata'', a new species of the Xanthorrhoeaceae from Queensland |journal=[[Kew Bulletin]] |volume=37 |issue=2 |pages=229–235 |jstor=4109965}}</ref>
